INSERT INTO events VALUES(33,'Stanford Preservation & Structural Rhinoplasty Course 2025','stanford preservation structural rhinoplasty course 2025','2025-11-13T16:00:00.000Z',NULL,'500 Pasteur Dr500, Pasteur DrivePalo Alto, CA 94304','$400 â€“ $1,700','Join the Stanford Preservation & Structural Rhinoplasty Course with Director Sam Most, MD. Get hands-on expert training.Overview:We invite you to be part of a unique educational opportunity at the 2025 Stanford Preservation and Structural Rhinoplasty Course (SPSRC 2025). This exclusive course offers a rare chance to learn from world-renowned faculty in the field of Preservation Rhinoplasty, including Drs. Robotti, Goksel, Rohrich, and other leading experts. Dr. Sam Most, one of the most ','Join the Stanford Preservation & Structural Rhinoplasty Course with Director Sam Most, MD. Get hands-on expert training.Overview:We invite you to be part of a unique educational opportunity at the 2025 Stanford Preservation and Structural Rhinoplasty Course (SPSRC 2025). This exclusive course offers a rare chance to learn from world-renowned faculty in the field of Preservation Rhinoplasty, including Drs. Robotti, Goksel, Rohrich, and other leading experts. Dr. Sam Most, one of the most published authorities on preservation techniques, will serve as the course director.Faculty:Sam P. Most, MD (Course Director)Enrico Robotti, MD (Guest of Honor)Abdulkadir GÃ¶ksel, MD (Guest of Honor)Rod Rohrich, MD (Guest of Honor)Roxana Cobo, MD (Grand Rounds Speaker)Fausto Lopez Ulloa, MDOren Friedman, MDPriyesh Patel, MDIvan Wayne, MDStuart Geldenhuys, MDBrian Wong, MDJose Barrera, MDJon-Paul Pepper, MDSeth Davis, MD& MoreCourse Highlights:Lecture Sessions (Two Days):Engage in an intensive two-day program filled with expert lectures and recorded live surgeries, offering invaluable insights into the latest preservation rhinoplasty techniques. Our esteemed faculty, including pioneers like Drs. Robotti, Goksel, and Rohrich, will guide you through cutting-edge approaches and share their unparalleled clinical expertise.Laboratory Session (Half-Day):On the third day, experience a hands-on lab session dedicated to mentored cadaver dissections. This rare opportunity allows participants to perform dissections under the guidance of course faculty. Instruments will be provided, and all attendees will have the chance to work with fresh cadaver specimens in a focused, small-group setting. Due to the intimate nature of this course, lab space is limited, ensuring personalized instruction.Why Attend:This course is specifically designed for rhinoplasty surgeons in Facial Plastic Surgery, or Plastic Surgery who want to stay at the forefront of Preservation Rhinoplasty techniques. Whether you''re seeking to refine your skills or update your knowledge, SPSRC 2025 offers an exceptional opportunity to enhance your practice and expand your surgical capabilities. Note: this is a non-CME event.Limited Enrollment:To maintain the highest quality of learning and ensure personalized attention, we are limiting enrollment for both the lecture and lab portions of the course. Donâ€™t miss your chance to learn from the best in the field and secure your spot today. Register now for SPSRC 2025 and experience a truly special and intimate educational event.Locations:Day 1-2 (lecture course):500P Rooftop Garden Assembly Hall 500 Pasteur Dr, Palo Alto, CA 94304Day 3 (1/2 day laboratory):Center for Clinical Sciences ResearchMain Dissection Lab269 Campus Drive, Stanford CA 94305Cost and Registration: Included in registration fees are two days of lectures and one half-day lab, course materials, breakfast, lunch, and refreshments.Note that this is a non-CME opportunity.Early-bird available through June 30:Lectures Only (Day 1-2): $695 (Regular: $895)Lecture & Lab (Day 1-3): $1,295 (Regular: $1,695)Non-Stanford OHNS Residents - Lecture Only: $275 (Regular: $350)Non-Stanford OHNS Residents - Lecture & Lab: $550 (Regular: $695)Stanford OHNS Residents: Complimentary (you must register with your Stanford e-mail address).Payment Information:No refundsPlease complete the online registration form and select the payment option you prefer.Registration will NOT be guaranteed until payment is received. Credit card payment online is recommended.Parking: The closest parking lot to 500P: Pasteur Visitor Garage200 Pasteur Dr, Palo Alto, CA 94304Accommodations: Participants are asked to arrange for their lodging at nearby hotels.The Westin Palo Alto675 El Camino Real, Palo Alto, CA 94301(650)321-4422Sheraton Palo Alto Hotel625 El Camino Real, Palo Alto, CA 94301(650)321-2800Stanford Guest House2575 Sand Hill Road, Menlo Park, CA 94025(650)926-2800Please plan to arrive during registration time between 7:00 AM and 7:30AMPlease contact Marlena Sandoval - marlenas@stanford.edu - if you have any inquiries.Read moreCategory: Health, Medical','https://www.eventbrite.com/e/stanford-preservation-structural-rhinoplasty-course-2025-tickets-1290225131099?aff=ebdssbneighborhoodbrowse',NULL,'eventbrite','music',0,'2025-11-03T21:41:15.198Z','2025-11-10_to_2025-11-16',0,'æ–¯å¦ç¦ä¿ç•™ä¸ç»“æ„æ€§é¼»æ•´å½¢è¯¾ç¨‹ 2025å¹´');
