INSERT INTO events VALUES(76,'Voices of Change: a DEI&B Lunch Roundtable','voices of change a dei b lunch roundtable','2025-11-11T19:30:00.000Z',NULL,'OneDigital19200 Stevens Creek Boulevard##110, Cupertino, CA 95014','Free','Join us online via Zoom or in person for an insightful and interactive program.Bay Area Human Resources Connections (baHRC) is pleased to collaborate with OneDigital''s Kristen Eskew, Vice President, Diversity, Equity, Inclusion & Belonging, to present this hybrid event to the HR Community.OVERVIEW âœ¨Listen. Reflect. Act.Join us for OneDigital''s DEI&B RoundTable to explore the evolving landscape of Diversity, Equity, Inclusion, and Belonging. We''ll discuss where organizations are today, wh','Join us online via Zoom or in person for an insightful and interactive program.Bay Area Human Resources Connections (baHRC) is pleased to collaborate with OneDigital''s Kristen Eskew, Vice President, Diversity, Equity, Inclusion & Belonging, to present this hybrid event to the HR Community.OVERVIEW âœ¨Listen. Reflect. Act.Join us for OneDigital''s DEI&B RoundTable to explore the evolving landscape of Diversity, Equity, Inclusion, and Belonging. We''ll discuss where organizations are today, whatâ€™s changing, and whatâ€™s next.TAKEAWAYS âœ¨Enjoy a thoughtful conversation with peers who share your passion for cultivating inclusive, high-performing workplaces while breaking bread at a casual luncheon at OneDigital in Cupertino, CA, or join us virtually via Zoom or at another OneDigital Walnut Creek location.Presenter: Kristen Eskew, Vice President, Diversity, Equity, Inclusion & BelongingKristen Eskew is the VP of Diversity, Equity, Inclusion, and Belonging (DEI&B) at OneDigital, a leading insurance brokerage, financial services, and HR consulting firm. In her role, Kristen drives OneDigitalâ€™s DEI&B strategy across the organization. Before becoming VP of DEI&B, she served in a regional leadership role that aligned with all things growth: DEI&B, talent, and business development. Before OneDigital, she worked in talent and leadership at Consolidated Planning, a prominent financial planning firm in the Southeast, and spearheaded their DEI&B journey.Born in California and raised in a military family in Georgia and North Carolina, Kristen attended the University of North Carolina at Wilmington, earning a B.A. in Communications Studies. She now calls Charlotte, NC, home. Kristen is a super-connector whose passion for people shines not only in her work in DEI&B, business development, and talent acquisition, but also in her community involvement. Kristen serves on the board of Neighborhood Hope and Youth Development Initiatives, both Charlotte-based non-profits. In addition, she serves on the advisory board for Yellowbird, a financial empowerment platform that provides underserved communities with quality access to financial literacy.Enthusiastic about being a culture changer and making an impact, Kristen enjoys serving as a featured speaker, moderator, and panelist at colleges, business events, and diversity seminars. She has been quoted in multiple media publications, including Forbes and Insurance News Net.In her spare time, Kristen loves cookingâ€”and eating!, trail running, and practicing her interior design skills. A happy wife to husband Josh, and proud aunt of seven nieces and nephews, Kristen also enjoys being a dog mom to Teddy and Maggie.Sponsor: OneDigital, a leading provider of employee benefits and HR solutions, proudly sponsors this event. OneDigital''s sponsorship highlights its commitment to advancing HR practices and supporting professionals in navigating digital transformation. If you''re passionate about HR and eager to drive change, this could be a fantastic opportunity to deepen your knowledge and skills.Read moreCategory: Business, Educators','https://www.eventbrite.com/e/voices-of-change-a-deib-lunch-roundtable-tickets-1909649024639?aff=ebdssbcitybrowse',NULL,'eventbrite','music',0,'2025-11-05T18:19: