INSERT INTO events VALUES(287,'MingKwai, Rediscovered','mingkwai rediscovered','2025-12-02T17:00:00.000Z',NULL,'Green Library (Silicon Valley Archives), 557 Escondido Mall, Stanford, CA 94305','Free','The legendary MingKwai Chinese Typewriter has been found. On December 2, Stanford will reintroduce it to the world. WAITLIST NOW OPEN!WAITLIST NOW OPEN | DON''T FORGET TO JOIN THE WAITLIST Join us on December 2, 2025, as we explore the origins of of the incredible MingKwai typewriter, trace its history across continents, and examine its lasting cultural and technological impact.The MingKwai Chinese Typewriter, a milestone in the history of Chinese information technology, was invented by the','The legendary MingKwai Chinese Typewriter has been found. On December 2, Stanford will reintroduce it to the world. WAITLIST NOW OPEN!WAITLIST NOW OPEN | DON''T FORGET TO JOIN THE WAITLIST Join us on December 2, 2025, as we explore the origins of of the incredible MingKwai typewriter, trace its history across continents, and examine its lasting cultural and technological impact.The MingKwai Chinese Typewriter, a milestone in the history of Chinese information technology, was invented by the Chinese-born author, translator, and cultural commentator Lin Yutang in the 1940s. Discovered in a New York basement, this extraordinary prototype has been entrusted to the Stanford University Libraries, where it will be used in research, exhibits, and academic programs.To celebrate the typewriterâ€™s rediscovery and new home at Stanford, we will be bringing together scholars and experts from across multiple disciplines to reintroduce the legendary MingKwai Chinese Typewriter to the world. Dr. Thomas S. Mullaney, Professor of Chinese History at Stanford University, will lead a team of researchers and students in exploring the MingKwai''s historical, technological, and cultural significance.Read moreCategory: Community, Other','https://www.eventbrite.com/e/mingkwai-rediscovered-tickets-175237942